comment: Tobacco plate with a peach finish
While I prefer Redbreast for normal Irish enjoyment, this whiskey was simply delicious. It had a great nose, medium peat with a bit of pepper and spice.

Nose: honey, charred, vanilla, clean linen
Palate: oily, meaty, almost fresh laundry
Finish: sweet finish, somewhat smooth, bacon/sausage flavor

One of the better Bushmills - lightly charred oak, ripe pear, sugary breakfast cereal (the kind that makes Dr. Atkins roll over his grave), and a light spiciness on the back of the palate.

Good stuff.
Tastes like Jamo with a bit more complexity and barrel.
Smooth easy whiskey. Soft start nice finish
